


05/27/2021 - Practice 5 - Loops and Character Class

ASCII
space -> 32
digits -> 48 to 57 both included
uppercase letters -> 65 to 90 both included
lowercase letters -> 97 to 122 both included

Instead of ASCII, we can use Character class methods to run some specific programs, especially when we are curious about a char being uppercase, lowercase, digit, letter or so.

1. isLetter(char) -> this method takes a char as argument and returns a boolean. It determines whether the specified char value is a letter


2. isDigit(char) -> this method takes a char as argument and returns a boolean. It determines whether the specified char value is a digit


3. isLetterOrDigit(char) -> this method takes a char as argument and returns a boolean. It determines whether the specified char value is a letter or a digit


4. isWhitespace(char) -> this method takes a char as argument and returns a boolean. It determines whether the specified char value is a white space


5. isLowerCase(char) -> this method takes a char as argument and returns a boolean. It determines whether the specified char value is a lowercase letter


6. isUpperCase(char) -> this method takes a char as argument and returns a boolean. It determines whether the specified char value is an uppercase letter













